{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fdf750b2-f2ae-426b-9dd0-e146893e04b9","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for the testing platform works by running the test project as an executable. When you use `dotnet run`, the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package watches for file changes and automatically re-runs affected tests without a full rebuild.\n\n`dotnet test` performs a one-shot build-and-run cycle, so it won't keep the process alive to watch for changes.\n\n```bash\n# With TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED already set:\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a8772ee0-ced5-431a-b3b7-dec831d2021e","outputTokens":139,"requestId":"67C2:13C959:2BE4AE5:30A127D:69FD41B5"},"id":"c874a1a7-795a-481a-a922-03ca8a31cd49","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:51:58.611Z","parentId":"37b28187-fcfc-496e-bc63-cea58cadc396"}
